# Thoughts Journal System

The user maintains a daily journal at `<thoughts-dir>/` (the placeholder is resolved by `journal-config.local.mdc`; if that file is absent, treat `<thoughts-dir>` as `~/code/thoughts/`). It contains:

- `<thoughts-dir>/daily/YYYY-MM-DD.md` — daily session logs, plans, and notes
- `<thoughts-dir>/ideas.md` — persistent idea backlog
- `<thoughts-dir>/open-questions.md` — unresolved questions
- `<thoughts-dir>/decisions.md` — decision log with rationale
- `<thoughts-dir>/til.md` — things learned (canonical for TILs; session-summarize appends here)
- `<thoughts-dir>/parking-lot.md` — deferred / out-of-scope items to revisit later
- `<thoughts-dir>/weekly/` — weekly retrospective rollups (`YYYY-WNN.md`)
- `<thoughts-dir>/projects/` — per-project running notes

At the end of a session the user may ask to summarize and log the session. The `session-summarize` skill handles this. Do not proactively invoke it — wait for the user to ask.
